—- 46. Qui saepe, Sco. Sotades : 'O πένης ἐλεεῒται, ὁ δὲ πλούσιος 1 φθονεῖται. Judges are often, through eompassion, biassed to the ’ poor; and sometimes, through envy, unjustly decide against the rich. Though compassion and pity have something noble and generous in them, and deserve to be cherished, yet they ought never to influence our judgment, so far as to make us swerve from a steady adherence to justice. Hence, in that divine system of laws given to the Israelites, this is particularly cautioned against. See Leviticus xix. 15.
